<TITLE> NBR sues M K Alamgir </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 21 (bdnews24.com)  The National Board of Revenue on Sunday sued former Awami League state minister Mohiuddin Khan Alamgir for allegedly dodging Tk 53.14 lakh in tax. A tax official, AKM Shahadat Hossain, filed the case with the Dhaka metropolitan senior special judge's court in the afternoon. According to the case details, the former state minister for planning hid information on property worth Tk 2.12 crore in fiscal 2002-03 and evaded tax on it. Alamgir is now in jail. Judge Md Azizul Huq ordered jail authorities to take Alamgir to the court on Sept 4 for appearance.
